                                 Herbalism

    Herbalism lets you gather herbs from terrain across the world. Herbs
are saved as profession materials and are used by Alchemy, work orders,
guildcraft preparations, and some recipe cards.

Getting started:
  1. Buy profession tools in the profession building, 4e, n from Center of
     Town.
  2. Travel to a natural area.
  3. Use 'gather herbs'.
  4. Use 'reagents' or 'reagents herb' to review saved herbs.

    Terrain matters. Different herbs are associated with different outdoor
areas, and some are more useful for certain potion or guildcraft recipes.
Use 'reagents search <herb>' when you want hints about where something
comes from, and 'professions gathering' for a command overview.

    Herbalism can also be worked indirectly. In the profession building,
you can hire herbalism workers for a terrain target. Workers bring back
materials over time and take their payment from your bank account.

Useful commands:
  gather herbs
  reagents herb
  reagents search Rose Hip
  professions gathering
  professions check potion str1
  help alchemy
  help workers

    Druids can use their silver sickle instead of a gardening spade.
